{
  "id": "t3rZrJqo",
  "slug": "bodies-bodies",
  "title": "Bodies! Bodies!",
  "description": "No more items despawning, if you die, your dead body will lay on the cold hard ground waiting for you.",
  "body": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\">This mod requires</span></span> <span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-api\">Fabric API</a></span></span><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\">,</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\"> and is compatible with</span></span> <span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/trinkets\">Trinkets</a>.</span></p>\n<center>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\">JOIN OUR DISCORD!</span></strong></span><br><a title=\"discord invite\" href=\"https://discord.com/invite/G4PjhEf\"><em><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://discordapp.com/api/guilds/707435077679841350/embed.png?style=banner2&amp;v=2\" width=\"337\" height=\"80\" /></em></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\">SUPPORT ME ON MY PATREON!</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/notsteven\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/5Wog2kV.png\" width=\"339\" height=\"69\" /></span></a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong>NEED A SERVER?</strong></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><a href=\"https://bisecthosting.com/notsteven\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"https://www.bisecthosting.com/partners/custom-banners/e4c02994-c687-4670-84d8-2bbbf94721e9.webp\" alt=\"bisect\" width=\"900\" height=\"142\" /></span></a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">When you die, your body will lay on the floor storing your items waiting for you to collect them</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/9SP4Ilc.png\" width=\"466\" height=\"466\" /></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">By default, only you can access your loot during the hour after your death. This can be tweaked using the config file.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">You can use Sneak + Right Click to instantly collect all your items or just Right Click to open the dead body's inventory.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/6LyfQPw.png\" width=\"571\" height=\"474\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\">If you have Trinkets installed, you can click the \"Trinkets\" button to see the Trinkets you had equipped. Sneaking + Right Clicking will also place your Trinkets in the correct slot.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Opped players can see a player's recent death history using the command \"/deathhistory [&lt;player&gt;]\"</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/czMUvcF.png\" width=\"424\" height=\"539\" /></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"></center><strong>In case of issues,</strong> everytime a player dies, a backup of their full data is made and stored. An opped player can use the command \"/restorebackup &lt;deathId&gt;\". The deathId is printed on the log after a player dies. </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Old entries are moved to a different data file, which can be found within the world's save folder. You can see them using NBT Editor if needed.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Note that if you find a consistent way of reproducing an issue which would require an opped player to restore their data, please report the issue on GitHub!</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n",
